The administration of Governor Ifeanyi Ugwuanyi of Enugu State has assured Osun governor-elect, Ademola Adeleke, that Enugu State is his second home. This is contained in a statement signed by the Secretary to the State Government, Simon Ortuanya, provided to journalists on Thursday in Enugu. Governor Ugwuanyi expressed happiness over Mr Adeleke’s victory in the keenly contested 2022 Osun State Governorship Election on July 16. According to Mr Ugwuanyi, Adeleke is “not only from Osun State but also from Enugu State where he was born”. “The people of Enugu State welcome your victory and will receive you with open arms at your convenience. “The electoral victory of Adeleke is a big vote of confidence, by the great people of Osun State, in your capacity and competence to turn fortunes around in the state. “The government and good people of Enugu State are happy and proud of the victory of our son, Sen. Ademola Adeleke,” the governor said. Gov. Ugwuanyi in the statement said the victory was an affirmation of the power of perseverance, abiding faith in God and a referendum on Mr Adeleke’s long-standing investment in human capital development. (NAN) Donate TEXT AD: Call Willie - +2348098788999 